;; Grand Unified Placemat — the Krowne Prism
;;
;; Three faces of sustainability (Krowne 2003, Fig 16.1):
;;   :V-people  → UKRN-S (participatory sustainability)
;;   :V-money   → VSAT   (fiscal sustainability)
;;   :V-orgs    → FUTON  (organizational sustainability)
;;
;; Each vertex is extruded along the I0→I4 maturity axis.
;; The triangle becomes a prism; the prism is the value model.
;;
;; Inter-edges are typed flows (Krowne's a–f, updated).
;; Diagonal inter-edges are data-producing practices that live
;; in multiple systems simultaneously.
;;
;; Genealogy:
;;   Krowne 2003 (Fig 16.1 — the triangle that wants to be a voxel)
;;   Corneli & Krowne 2005 (scholium-based document model)
;;   Corneli 2026 (equity loop, invariant layers, this composition)
;;
;; Projections (the Seven Faces):
;;   Each TikZ placemat is a 2D projection of this prism.
;;   The UKRN placemat projects the :V-people face.
;;   The FUTON devmap projects the :V-orgs face.
;;   The VSATLATARIUM *is* the :V-money face rendered as a 3D planetarium.
;;   Cross-face projections yield the inter-edge diagrams.

{:mission/id :grand-unified-placemat
 :mission/state :design
 :mission/date "2026-03-23"

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; VERTICES — the three faces of sustainability
 ;; =====================================================================

 :vertices
 [{:id :V-people
   :name "Participatory sustainability"
   :system "UKRN-S training ecosystem"
   :model-file "ukrns-value-model.edn"
   :krowne-vertex "People"
   :primacy true
   :note "Krowne: the one leg you cannot remove"}

  {:id :V-money
   :name "Fiscal sustainability"
   :system "VSAT / VSATLAS"
   :model-file nil ;; to be created: vsat-value-model.edn
   :krowne-vertex "Money"
   :note "Billable work with a real client; the thing that pays for itself"}

  {:id :V-orgs
   :name "Organizational sustainability"
   :system "FUTON stack"
   :model-file "futon-stack-invariant-model.edn"
   :krowne-vertex "Organizations"
   :note "Rules for coordination, not a legal entity (Jacobs 2026, slide 17)"}]

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; INVARIANT AXIS — the depth that makes the triangle a prism
 ;; Each vertex is extruded along I0→I4.
 ;; Named generically; each face instantiates differently.
 ;; =====================================================================

 :invariant-axis
 [{:id :I0
   :name "The core fact holds"
   :ukrns "Training produces capability change"
   :futon "Data persists durably"
   :vsat  "Stories are created and experienced"
   :note  "If this doesn't hold, nothing above it matters"}

  {:id :I1
   :name "The core fact is detectable"
   :ukrns "Capability change is detectable (T1 instrument)"
   :futon "State transitions are valid"
   :vsat  "Connections between stories become visible (interpretive layer)"
   :note  "Without detection the system is flying blind"}

  {:id :I2
   :name "Evidence reaches the people who need it"
   :ukrns "Interview data reaches trainers, CoP, institutions"
   :futon "Failures are visible and locatable"
   :vsat  "Interpretive links circulate — users see how stories relate"
   :note  "Detection that stays in a filing cabinet is not feedback"}

  {:id :I3
   :name "Feedback improves practice"
   :ukrns "Materials updated, delivery adapted, curriculum evolves"
   :futon "Work is structured — outputs land where they belong"
   :vsat  "Community interpretation refines the atlas over time"
   :note  "The system learns from its own experience"}

  {:id :I4
   :name "The system sustains itself"
   :ukrns "Equity loop closes: contribution → governance → capability"
   :futon "The stack governs itself without folklore or heroics"
   :vsat  "Stewardship layer closes the loop: moderation, governance, commons"
   :note  "Participatory sustainability is the one leg you cannot remove"}]

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; KROWNE FLOWS — typed edges between vertices (updated from Fig 16.1)
 ;; These are the triangle's edges; each has two directions.
 ;; =====================================================================

 :krowne-flows
 [;; --- People ↔ Money ---

  {:id :F-a
   :krowne-label "a. advertising"
   :from :V-people :to :V-money
   :instantiation "Publications, working papers, the VSATLATARIUM as demo"
   :what-flows "Visibility of participatory work creates fiscal opportunity"
   :note "People's stories and evidence become the product's content"}

  {:id :F-b
   :krowne-label "b. fundraising"
   :from :V-money :to :V-people
   :instantiation "Research England, UKRN-S subscriptions, institutional co-investment"
   :what-flows "Revenue enables participation infrastructure"
   :note "Without funding the participation infrastructure doesn't exist"}

  ;; --- People ↔ Organizations ---

  {:id :F-c
   :krowne-label "c. audiences"
   :from :V-people :to :V-orgs
   :instantiation "T1 recipients, T3 trainers, VSAT users, academic readers"
   :what-flows "People's needs drive what the infrastructure must provide"
   :note "The infrastructure exists to serve these people"}

  {:id :F-d
   :krowne-label "d. content, services"
   :from :V-orgs :to :V-people
   :instantiation "Training materials, evaluation instruments, pattern libraries, planetarium"
   :what-flows "Infrastructure returns tools that enlarge people's capability to act"
   :note "Sen: conversion factors flow from organizational to participatory"}

  ;; --- Money ↔ Organizations ---

  {:id :F-e
   :krowne-label "e. sponsorship"
   :from :V-money :to :V-orgs
   :instantiation "Client contracts sustain stack development; VSAT revenue funds FUTON work"
   :what-flows "Fiscal sustainability enables organizational sustainability"
   :note "The client relationship is the bridge"}

  {:id :F-f
   :krowne-label "f. content purchase / license"
   :from :V-orgs :to :V-money
   :instantiation "OER Commons (CC BY), open source, VSAT deliverables, flexiarg exports"
   :what-flows "Organizational outputs that have market value"
   :note "Open licensing is the norm; professional services are the revenue"}]

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; DIAGONAL INTER-EDGES — data-producing practices that live in
 ;; multiple systems simultaneously. These are the edges that make
 ;; the prism more than three separate triangles.
 ;; =====================================================================

 :inter-edges
 [{:id :X-t1-instrument
   :name "T1 exit interview instrument"
   :type :practice-as-data
   :touches #{:V-people :V-orgs}
   :invariant :I1
   :ukrns-role "Detects capability change (Pattern 5 resolution)"
   :futon-role "Interview data stored in futon1a; argument validated by futon5"
   :vsat-role  "Interview narratives importable as stories in VSATLATARIUM"
   :note "Phase 3 of current project AND Iteration 1 of new approach"}

  {:id :X-pattern-library
   :name "Flexiarg pattern library"
   :type :knowledge-as-data
   :touches #{:V-people :V-orgs :V-money}
   :invariant :I3
   :ukrns-role "Five equity patterns structure the evaluation findings"
   :futon-role "Stored in futon3/library/equity/; validated by futon5 AIF²"
   :vsat-role  "Future: import as cosmos in VSATLATARIUM (flagged in CLAUDE.md)"
   :note "Patterns are simultaneously findings, design tools, and content"}

  {:id :X-contribution-log
   :name "Contribution log"
   :type :governance-as-data
   :touches #{:V-people :V-orgs}
   :invariant :I4
   :ukrns-role "Makes invisible labour visible; creates recognised standing"
   :futon-role "Analogous to the promotion loop: work → candidate → operational"
   :vsat-role  "Stewardship layer tracks who reviewed, linked, moderated"
   :note "The equity loop's accounting mechanism"}

  {:id :X-peer-evaluation
   :name "Cross-institutional peer evaluation"
   :type :practice-as-data
   :touches #{:V-people :V-money}
   :invariant :I1
   :ukrns-role "Pattern 5 heated-up resolution: trainers interview each other's recipients"
   :futon-role "Evidence chain modelled as hypergraph; validated end-to-end"
   :vsat-role  "Evaluation narratives become linked stories; patterns of harm/benefit visible"
   :note "Dissolves the monitoring collective action problem into reciprocal exchange"}

  {:id :X-vsatlatarium
   :name "VSATLATARIUM planetarium"
   :type :infrastructure-as-content
   :touches #{:V-money :V-orgs :V-people}
   :invariant :I2
   :ukrns-role "Evidence visualisation: training patterns rendered as constellation"
   :futon-role "Consumes Arxana hypergraphs (EDN → stories/scenes/links)"
   :vsat-role  "The deployed product; the thing clients pay for"
   :note "The planetarium IS the I2 invariant made visible — evidence reaching people"}

  {:id :X-open-knowledge
   :name "Knowledge as common good"
   :type :mission-as-edge
   :touches #{:V-people :V-orgs :V-money}
   :invariant :I4
   :ukrns-role "University's primary mission (Jacobs 2026): solve collective action problems"
   :futon-role "The stack's invariant architecture applied to social systems"
   :vsat-role  "VSATLAS stewardship: communities govern their own narrative commons"
   :note "Neil's framing: institution = rules for coordination. This edge IS the institution."}]

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; MATURITY SNAPSHOT — where each vertex sits on the I0→I4 axis
 ;; (point-in-time, 2026-03-23)
 ;; =====================================================================

 :maturity
 {:V-people {:I0 :unverified :I1 :absent :I2 :absent :I3 :absent :I4 :absent
             :note "T3 evaluation complete; T1 instrument designed; nothing operational yet"}
  :V-money  {:I0 :operational :I1 :building :I2 :building :I3 :aspirational :I4 :aspirational
             :note "VSAT deployed; interpretive layer in development; stewardship layer designed"}
  :V-orgs   {:I0 :operational :I1 :operational :I2 :operational :I3 :building :I4 :building
             :note "Inner invariants firm; outer layers actively being constructed"}}

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; KROWNE'S THESIS (updated)
 ;; =====================================================================

 :thesis
 "A system is sustainable when all three vertices reach I4 and the
  inter-edges carry typed flows between them. Participatory sustainability
  (:V-people) has primacy: it is the vertex you cannot remove, because
  it is tied directly to the definition of success (Krowne 2003, p.303).
  But primacy does not mean sufficiency. Without fiscal sustainability
  (:V-money), the participation infrastructure cannot be maintained.
  Without organizational sustainability (:V-orgs), the coordination
  rules that make participation productive cannot be enforced or evolved.
  The three vertices and their inter-edges form an irreducible structure.
  The invariant axis (I0→I4) measures how far each vertex has progressed
  from aspiration to self-sustaining operation. The Grand Unified Placemat
  is the prism that results: Krowne's triangle extruded along the
  maturity axis, with diagonal inter-edges connecting the faces."}
